3.00	Reuben_stoddard	Ruben Studdard	Christopher Theodore Ruben Studdard (born September 12, 1978), best known as Ruben Studdard, is an American R&amp;B, pop, and gospel singer. He rose to fame as winner of the second season of American Idol. He received a Grammy Award nomination in December 2003 for Best Male R&amp;B Vocal Performance for "Superstar."	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b8/Ruben_Studdard_2.jpg/220px-Ruben_Studdard_2.jpg
